  "texts": [
    "Model seems to do relatively poorly while generating layman summaries for fractures (categorized under Other Disease).",
    "This may be the result of relatively small representation (~10%) of such reports in the training set.",
    "While stable exams and metastatic disease also have similar representation in the dataset, their summarization is quite straightforward.",
    "In both cases, the patient needs to know their disease is unchanged, or their cancer has now spread.",
    "In case of fractures, there are many important pieces of information including anatomical location, severity, and any resulting complications (e.g., joint effusion/hemarthrosis)."
  ],
